<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-20T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-20T20:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/274</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-20T20:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            20, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2089. Your 2369, February 14, 2 [12] p.m., and referring Department’s
                                    2065.<note n="1" xml:id="d54fn1"><ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_381">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 381</ref>.</note> We desire progress with
                                Bolshevik authorities to be gradual. I do not believe that joint
                                protests are wise and am glad to learn your judgment has prompted
                                you to refrain from further action this character without express
                                authority.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>